ObjectStates.Name: Custom_Model_Bag
ObjectStates.LuaScript:
function onObjectLeaveContainer(container, object)

		   if container.getLock() and container == self then
     local clone = object.clone({position = {0,100,0}})
		        function coPause()
			            coroutine.yield(0)
			            container.putObject(clone)
			            return 1
        end
		    startLuaCoroutine(self, 'coPause')
    end	
	end

--[[
Wargame/Warhammer RPG TurnBased Movement System
Created by: A_Rittle_Bit_Sneaky


 moving marker Script (the white spinning marker) was originally created by Rodney. I have extensively modifed his script to improve the functionality drastically for wargames (his markers did not work well with models that had scaling applied to them, certain models the white marker was too huge)

]]

-- customize variables
markerScale = 0.4
markerColor = {1, 1, 1}
markerRemainingTime = 10


frameInterval = 0.01
rotationDegreePerFrame = 1

-- global variables
markerObject = nil
rotationTimerId = nil
fadeOutTimerId = nil
movementTimer1= nil

rewindPosition = {}
rewindDistance = 0
rewindDistanceSwap = 0

lastBottomLevel = 1.5

movingMarkerVersion = "2016092000"

playercolor2 = "White"
-- constants
hidePosition = {0, -300, 0}
hideScale = {0.1, 0.1, 0.1}

-- events
function onLoad()
   initializeTimer()
   createObjects()
end

function onDestroy()
   removeTimers()
   deleteObjects()
   
end

function onCollisionEnter(info)
   updateBottomLevel(info.contact_points)
end

function onPickedUp(color)

rewindPosition = self.getPosition()
   removeTimers()
   setMarker()
   findDistanceMoved()
   --createMovementTimer()
   playercolor2 = color
end

function onDropped()
   fadeOutMarker()
   --setObjectNill used to tell the distance function that the object is nolonger being moved.
   setObjectNill()
   buttonOnDrop()
   removeLowerButtons()
   
   --reset the global variables used to rewind objects
 rewindDistance = movement
 removeMovementTimer()
 rewindDistanceSwap = 0
end

-- internal functions

function createObjects()
   markerObject = spawnObject({
         type = "Custom_Model",
         position = hidePosition,
         rotation = {0, 0, 0},
         scale = hideScale
   })

   markerObject.setCustomObject({
         type = "Generic",
         mesh = "http://pastebin.com/raw/RBUFj0HE",
         collider = "http://pastebin.com/raw/bUwzJeWz"
   })
   
   markerObject.setColorTint(markerColor)
   markerObject.interactable = false
   markerObject.lock()
end

function deleteObjects()
   markerObject.destruct()
end

function updateBottomLevel(points)
   local updated = false
   local currentBottomLevel = self.getPosition().y

   for i, v in ipairs(points) do
      if v[2] < currentBottomLevel then
         updated = true
         currentBottomLevel = v[2]
      end
   end

   if updated then
      lastBottomLevel = currentBottomLevel
   end
end   

function setMarker()
   local pos = self.getPosition()
   local scale = self.getScale()
   

   markerObject.setPosition({pos.x, lastBottomLevel + 0.2, pos.z})
   markerObject.setScale({1, 10, 1})

   
   if frameInterval <= 0 then
      frameInterval = 0.1
   end

   Timer.create({
         identifier = rotationTimerId,
         function_name = "rotateMarker",
         function_owner = self,
         parameters = {
            degree = rotationDegreePerFrame
         },
         delay = frameInterval,
         repetitions = 0
   })
end

--+++++Start+++++++++++
--function to rewind the model to its previous position. This is the On click function for the button attached to the Object Marker
function rewindMove()
local currentPos = self.getPosition()
local num = rewindDistance

rewindDistance = rewindDistanceSwap
rewindDistanceSwap = num
self.setPosition(rewindPosition)

rewindPosition = currentPos
	if  Global.Call('getDisplayOption') == "Remove" then
	else
		updateMoveDistanceDisplay(rewindDistance)
	end

--update the display to reflect how far the object moved after the rewind
if rewindDistance == 0 then
 markerObject.editButton({index=0, position = {0, 0.5, 0}, height=800, width=800, color = {0,0,1}, label = "Rewind"})
 else
  markerObject.editButton({index=0, position = {0, 0, 0}, height=200, width=200, color = {1,0,0}})
  end
end
--*********  END ********************

--+++++Start+++++++++++
function findDistanceMoved()
targetPos= self.getPosition()
 
object = 1 --set object to 1 so that distance function can start




	function createMovementTracker()
	self.clearButtons()
	markerObject.clearButtons()


		local largeFont = 400
		local buttonBoxSize = 200
		local white = {1,1,1}
		local black = {0,0,0}
		
		--rescale the scale for the button to scale of 1. This is neccessary because buttons scale is multiplied by the scale of the objects
	rescaledX=1/self.getScale().x
	rescaledY=1/self.getScale().y
	rescaledZ=1/self.getScale().z

	--This sets the height of the display to a static 5 inches high. Neccessary because position of buttons is multiplied by the scaling applied to objects. Would like to try adding the object bounds to get it just 1 inch outside of the object bounds
	
	local x2 = self.getScale().x
	local y2 = self.getScale().y
	local z2 = self.getScale().z
	
	local boundsY= self.getBounds().size.y
	local boundsZ= self.getBoundsNormalized().size.z
	
	local buttonPosY= 5/y2
	local buttonPosZ= ((boundsZ+1)/z2)/2


		
		self.createButton({index=0,
		label=" ", click_function = "pov", font_color = white,
		function_owner = self,  position={0, buttonPosY, 0}, rotation = {0,0,0}, scale = {rescaledX, rescaledY, rescaledZ}, height=200, width=300,
		font_size = largeFont, color = Global.Call('getDisplayColor'), tooltip = "click for POV"
		})
		self.createButton({index=1,
		label=" ", click_function = "pov", font_color = white,
		function_owner = self,  position={0, 0.2/y2, buttonPosZ}, rotation = {0,180,0}, scale = {rescaledX, rescaledY, rescaledZ}, height=1, width=1,
		font_size = largeFont, color = Global.Call('getDisplayColor'), tooltip = "click for POV", alignment = 5
		})
		self.createButton({index=2,
		label=" ", click_function = "pov", font_color = white,
		function_owner = self,  position={0, 0.2/y2, -buttonPosZ}, rotation = {0,180,0}, scale = {rescaledX, rescaledY, rescaledZ}, height=1, width=1,
		font_size = largeFont, color = Global.Call('getDisplayColor'), tooltip = "click for POV", alignment = 3
		})
		
		markerObject.createButton({index=0,
		label=" ", click_function = "rewindMove", font_color = white,
		function_owner = self,  position= {0, 0, 0}, scale = {1,0.1,1}, height=200, width=200,
		font_size = 300, color = {1,0,0}, tooltip = "rewind", alignment = 3
		})		
		


	end


	function updateMoveDistanceDisplay(movementDistance)
	   
		self.editButton({index=0, label= movementDistance})
	end
	
	function updateMoveDistanceDisplayLower(movementDistance)
		self.editButton({index=1, label= movementDistance})
		self.editButton({index=2, label= movementDistance})
	end
	
	function changeMoveButtonFaded()
	      
		self.editButton({index=0, color = Global.Call('getDisplayFade')})
	   
	end






--create the button that displays the move values
createMovementTracker()


	
movementTimer1= "movementTimer".."_" .. getUniqueID() .. self.guid


Timer.create({
         identifier = movementTimer1,
         function_name = "movementNumbersUpdate",
         function_owner = self,
		 delay=0.1,
         repetitions = 0,
   })
		
	
end
--*********  END ********************

--+++++Start+++++++++++
--Rounding function to round to the nearest tenth of a decimal
function round(num, dec)
    local mult = 10^(dec or 0)
    return math.floor(num * mult + 0.5) / mult
end
--*********  END ********************

--+++++Start+++++++++++
function rotateMarker(param)
   markerObject.setRotation({0, markerObject.getRotation().y + param.degree, 0})
end

function fadeOutMarker()
   if markerRemainingTime <= 0 then
      markerRemainingTime = 0.1
   end

   Timer.create({
         identifier = fadeOutTimerId,
         function_name = "hideMarker",
         function_owner = self,
         delay = markerRemainingTime,
   })
end
--*********  END ********************

--+++++Start+++++++++++
function hideMarker()
   
   Timer.destroy(rotationTimerId)
   markerObject.setPosition(hidePosition)
   markerObject.setScale(hideScale)
end
--*********  END ********************



--+++++Start+++++++++++
function initializeTimer()
   -- workaround for guid/copy&paste bug.
   -- join random id to guid.
   rotationTimerId = self.guid .. "_" .. getUniqueID() ..  "__fadeOut__"
   fadeOutTimerId = self.guid .. "_" .. getUniqueID() ..  "__rotation__"

   removeTimers()
end   
--*********  END ********************

--+++++Start+++++++++++
function getUniqueID()
   return string.format("%s-%s", os.date("%Y%m%d%H%M%S"), math.random(100))
end

--+++++Start+++++++++++
function removeTimers()
   Timer.destroy(rotationTimerId)
   Timer.destroy(fadeOutTimerId)
end
--*********  END ********************
--+++++Start+++++++++++
--Function to decide what happens to the movement display when the object is dropped
function buttonOnDrop()

	if Global.Call('getDisplayOption') == "Fade" then

		changeMoveButtonFaded()

	elseif Global.Call('getDisplayOption') == "Remove" then
		removeTopDisplay()
	end
               --[[ I will eventually change this to a removeButton() so that we only remove the moveDisplay button.this makes sure if they use mutliple scripts(health Counter or other trackers for models) that they don't lose those buttons too --]]
 end
--*********  END ********************
--+++++Start+++++++++++
 --Changes player camera to the position of the model
function pov()

	local rotate = self.getRotation()

	Player[playercolor2].lookAt({position = self.getPosition(), pitch = 10, distance = 10, yaw = rotate.y})
end
--*********  END ********************
--+++++Start+++++++++++
function removeTopDisplay()
	self.removeButton(0)
end
--*********  END ********************
--used as a flag on the drop function to tell the distance function to stop
function setObjectNill()
	object = 0
end



function removeLowerButtons()
self.removeButton(1)
self.removeButton(2)

end

function doNothing()

end



function removeMovementTimer()

Timer.destroy(movementTimer1)

end

function movementNumbersUpdate()
if object == 0 then
		else
			 objectPos = self.getPosition()
			 xDistance = math.abs(targetPos.x - objectPos.x)
			 zDistance = math.abs(targetPos.z - objectPos.z)
			 distance = xDistance^2 + zDistance^2
			 movement = math.sqrt(distance)
			
			 movement = round(movement,1)
			 updateMoveDistanceDisplay(movement)
			 updateMoveDistanceDisplayLower(movement)
			
		end
end
